    "value": "The Proton-M is an expendable Russian heavy-lift launch vehicle built by Khrunichev and derived from the Soviet-era Proton rocket, flown from Baikonur Cosmodrome since its first launch on 7 April 2001. Commercial missions are marketed by International Launch Services. The type has flown 116 times with 105 successes as of February 2026, carrying government and commercial satellites to geostationary transfer orbit as well as modules to the International Space Station, including the Nauka laboratory in July 2021.",
